  "text": "Threats to internal validity concern co-factors that could influence our results, and they are mainly related to various measurement settings used in our study. For RQ 3 , we choose the Bunch settings used by other approaches in the literature [CITATION_1] , although we are aware that our results for RQ 3 could have changed if we used different settings. Also, to limit variability of the results due to randomness, we iterated the hill-climbing based modularization 30 times.",
